==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trionyx
<hw>Tri*on"yx</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ (see <er>Tri-</er>) + <?/ a claw.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
genus of fresh-water or river turtles which have the shell imperfectly
developed and covered with a soft leathery skin. They are noted for
their agility and rapacity. Called also <altname>soft
tortoise</altname>, <altname>soft-shell tortoise</altname>, and
<altname>mud turtle</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The common American species (<spn>Trionyx ferox</spn>
syn. <spn>Aspidonectus ferox</spn>) becomes over a foot in length and is
very voracious. Similar species are found in Asia and Africa.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trior</ent>⟦br⟧
